# Handoff checklist (mandatory before handoff)

When the user wants a handoff, or when you are writing or updating a handoff note (e.g. **`doc/handoff/HANDOFF-*.md`** or **`.cursor/handoff/handoff-*.md`** — both **gitignored**, not on **`main`**):

## When to create a handoff (timing)

- **Right time:** You are at a real stopping point: scope is done **or** you are intentionally handing off **mid-flight** with a clear label (e.g. **WIP**, **blocked**, **needs decision**).
- **Wrong time:** Do **not** write a handoff that reads “ship complete” if delivery is not actually finished (e.g. commits on `main` that were never pushed, **GitHub CI not green**, local CI only, or known follow-ups omitted). If work is incomplete, **say so explicitly** in **Ship status** or a **Not done** section at the top — not only in **Next up**.
- **Push + GitHub CI:** When `npm run ci` is green and you committed to **`main`**, run **`npm run push:main`** (or `git push origin main` then **`npm run ci:watch-gh`**) and **wait for GitHub Actions green** before ending or marking shipped — see **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** → *Git workflow* step **3**. Treat “pushed but GitHub CI not watched / failed” as **unfinished** unless the user asked to stop before the watch, or `gh`/push failed (record that explicitly).

**You must run all four and record results in the handoff note. Do not skip any.**

1. **Code review** — Use the **code-reviewer** skill (`.cursor/skills/code-reviewer/SKILL.md`). Review the changed or relevant code since last handoff (or main branch). Output PASS/WARN/FAIL and a short summary. Put the summary in the handoff note under **Code review**.
2. **Tech debt evaluation** — Use the **tech-debt-evaluator** skill (`.cursor/skills/tech-debt-evaluator/SKILL.md`). Assess current debt; produce prioritized list. Put the short summary or "Do first" items in the handoff note under **Tech debt**.
3. **Tests / coverage** — Run **`npm run ci`** (includes **`npm run lint`**, **`npm run format:check`**, Vitest, build, Playwright; see **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** / **TEST_PLAN.md**). Note whether Tier 1 is green and, if useful, a one-line summary. Put in the handoff note under **Code coverage** (or **Tests**).
4. **Project readiness (optional)** — If you maintain a readiness checklist or skill for this product, use it and put the summary under **Project readiness**. Otherwise note "N/A" or skip that section.

5. **Tier 2 (integration / E2E) if needed** — If you added or changed behavior that requires integration or E2E validation, run the Tier 2 command from TEST_PLAN.md. Note in the handoff whether Tier 2 was run and the result. See `.cursor/rules/testing.mdc` and TEST_PLAN.md.

6. **Git commit + push + GitHub CI** — If the first four checks passed: bump version per [doc/VERSIONING.md](../../doc/VERSIONING.md) when shipping EDGE scope, stage, commit, then **`npm run push:main`** (or push + **`npm run ci:watch-gh`**). Record **GitHub Actions run URL/conclusion** in the handoff under **Tests / CI**. Treat “committed but not pushed” or “pushed but GitHub CI not green” as **unfinished** unless the user asked to stop early.

Then complete the rest of the handoff (update **PM_PLAN** / **EDGE plan** if product scope changed; **Done this session**, **Next up**, etc. in your **`doc/handoff/`** or `.cursor/handoff/` note — see **AGENT_HANDOFF.md**). When you summarize **Done this session** for humans, use the same **two-audience** idea as **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** → *Git workflow* step **3**: a short maintainer-oriented recap plus a **non-technical** “what someone using only the extension would notice” (see **techwriter** skill → *Dual-audience blurbs*).

**Filename and timestamp:** Prefer **`doc/handoff/HANDOFF-YYYY-MM-DD-HHmmss.md`** (local **24h** time, no colons — Windows-safe) so multiple handoffs per day get unique files. Add a **`Recorded:`** line under the H1 (ISO-8601 or local offset). See **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** → Source of truth → session notes.

## Chat response (mandatory — do not skip)

After the local note is written, **mirror a handoff starting point in chat**. The gitignored file alone is **not** a handoff for the user. Do **not** end with only “recorded at path X” or a link to the file.

**Required structure** (use these headings in order):

1. **One-line ship headline** — e.g. “**0.16.1** is shipped on `main` with green GitHub CI” or “**WIP** — …” if not shipped.
2. **`Recorded`** — local note path (`doc/handoff/HANDOFF-….md`, gitignored).
3. **Tracked doc sync** — bullet if **PM_PLAN.md** / **EDGE plan** changed on `main`; omit if none.
4. **`Ship status`** — table: Commit, Branch, GitHub CI (run URL + conclusion); add **Not done** row if push/CI incomplete.
5. **`Done this session`** — **two blurbs** (maintainer/plan, then extension-user) per **techwriter** *Dual-audience blurbs* — same content as the local note.
6. **`Next up (from handoff)`** — numbered or bulleted; include branch name / version hint for the next slice when known.
7. **Open items** — uncommitted tracked edits, UAT gates, review WARN follow-ups (optional line).

**Starting point for the next agent:** **Next up** must be actionable without opening the gitignored file (story id, backlog #, branch name, version target).

8. **`always.mdc` repo status** — Update the **Repo status** table in [`.cursor/rules/always.mdc`](../rules/always.mdc) (branch, shipped version, in-progress slice, last handoff path). Omit ephemeral **Uncommitted** rows once committed. Include this file in the same commit when handoff docs change on `main`, or in the next commit on the active feature branch.

See **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** → *Handoff protocol* and [`.cursor/handoff/_template.md`](../handoff/_template.md) → *Chat mirror*.
